misconceptions.inferred_category_name: Output format misinterpretation (always prints “Found at index” even when not found)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes the required output label is always “Found at index:” regardless of whether the target exists, and that printing -1 with that label is acceptable for the “not found” case.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: The problem statement specifies different required behavior for the not-found case: print -1 (typically without a misleading “Found at index:” message). While the search logic is correct, the output contract may be violated by always including the “Found at index:” prefix, which can be judged incorrect in strict autograding contexts.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: Potential wrong output (format mismatch) when T is not found: prints "Found at index: -1" instead of just "-1" (depending on expected output).
